Should you be worried that you might contract COVID-19 from handling or eating food?
• Can the coronavirus spread through food?
• Could I become ill from touching food packaging that is carrying the virus on its surface?
Another coronavirus, SARS-CoV-1, is known to be eliminated at cooking temperatures, says Erin Di Caprio, assistant specialist in UC Davis’ food science and technology department.
“I think people need to be reassured that food and things like that will be highly unlikely to be the source of this transmission,” Riley says.